svg.title: Photoelectric effect measurement apparatus - microscopic picture

cc:Work.dc:title: Photoelectric effect measurement apparatus - microscopic picture
cc:Work.dc:description: The photoelectron emitter (E) and collector (C) electrodes are placed in an evacuated quartz tube. When ultraviolet light hits the surface of the emitter, the ejected electrons are prevented from reaching the collector by a sufficiently low negative voltage, or helped to reach it by a positive voltage. The photoelectron current saturates when all emitted electrons (whose number depends on light intensity) are captured by the collector.
